CSS:

By attribute

<input type=text class=form_text>
<input type=email class=form_email>
input type=radio class=form_radio>

<div class="one two">
    <p> Two paragraphs total. </p>
    <p> Two paragraphs total. </p>
</div>

cssSelector:
1. input[class*=form] - input elements with type attribute CONTAINING the text form in the value
div[class*='one'] -> find all elements with div tag and class attribute should contain "one"!

2. input[class^=form] - input elements with the type attribute STARTING WITH form
div[class^='one'] -> find all elements with div tag and class attribute should start with "one"!

3. input[class$=radio] - input elements with type attribute ENDING WITH radio
div[class$='one'] -> find all elements with div tag and class attribute should end with "one"!